==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Gully
<hw>Gul"ly</hw>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>Gullies</plw>
<pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[<ets>Formerly gullet</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>A channel or hollow worn in the earth by a current of water; a
short deep portion of a torrent's bed when dry.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A grooved iron rail or tram plate.</def>
<mark>[Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Gully gut</b></col>, <cd>a glutton.</cd>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <au>Chapman.</au> -- <col><b>Gully hole</b></col>,
<cd>the opening through which gutters discharge surface
water.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gully</ent>⟦br⟧

